# 2021 Speedway Grand Prix of Czech Republic

The 2021 FIM Anlas Speedway Grand Prix of Czech Republic was the first and second races of the 2021 Speedway Grand Prix season. They took place on 16 & 18 July at the Mark√©ta Stadium in Prague, Czech Republic. The second Grand Prix had been scheduled for 17 July but was abandoned after 11 heats due to bad weather and held the following day. It was the 26th and 27th Speedway Grand Prix of Czech Republic. The calendar of events was disrupted by the effects of the COVID-19 pandemic.
The 26th event was won by Maciej Janowski (his eighth career Grand Prix win) and the 27th event was won by Artem Laguta (his second career Grand prix win).
